cc:Work.dc:title: Elvie #013
cc:Work.dc:description:
[Panel 1: Elvie is leaning on a pile of assembly language reference books]
Elvie: I'm learning to program using machine code -- -- but I'm struggling to *assemble* the *stack* of *pointers* I've *accumulated* and *register* them into *bits* of my *memory*…
[Panel 2: View of Elvie's room, with lots of noises from various sources both inside and outside] Elvie: …because there are too many *interrupts*!
